    • Constructor Detail

      • Rabbit

        public Rabbit​(boolean randomAge,
              Field field,
              Location location,
              int ba,
              double bp,
              int mls)
        Create a new rabbit. A rabbit may be created with age zero (a new born) or with a random age.
        Parameters:
        randomAge - If true, the rabbit will have a random age.
        field - The field currently occupied.
        location - The location within the field.
        ba - Breeding age passed from settings tab.
        bp - Breeding probability passed from settings tab.
        mls - Breeding probability passed from settings tab.

        Specified by:

        Parameters:

      • incrementAge

        private void incrementAge()
        Increase the age. This could result in the rabbit's death.

      • giveBirth

        private void giveBirth​(java.util.List<Animal> newRabbits)
        Check whether or not this rabbit is to give birth at this step if it is adjacent to a rabbit of the opposite gender. New births will be made into free adjacent locations.
        Parameters:
        newRabbits - A list to return newly born rabbits.

      • breed

        private int breed()
        Generate a number representing the number of births, if it can breed.
        Returns:
        The number of births (may be zero).

      • canBreed

        private boolean canBreed()
        A rabbit can breed if it has reached the breeding age and if female.
        Returns:
        true if the rabbit can breed, false otherwise.
